Dating: 3RD INTERMEDIATE PERIOD (not before); LATE PERIOD; LATE PERIOD (not after)
Name: Alabaster vase
Description: Alabaster vase with a rounded rim which thickens slightly towards the exterior and convex base. The upper third of the body presents two small symmetrically placed apendages serving as handles, rectangular in cross-section.  At the base small irregularities in the veining of the material can be observed.
